    <li><a href="/banks/capital-one/">Capital One</a> — Estate Administration: 1-888-810-4013</li>
  </ul>
</section>

<div class="can-wait">
  <strong>If you've done three or four things on this list, that's enough for today.</strong>
  The rest will be here tomorrow. The <a href="/timeline/first-month/">first month</a> list
  is where the formal account closures happen. This week is about notification and information-gathering.
</div>

<div class="emotional-note">
  <p>
    The first week often has a mechanical quality to it — phone calls, paperwork, logistics —
    that can feel like a strange protection from the grief underneath. Some people find it helpful
    to have tasks to do. Others find it unbearable that the world requires tasks right now.
    Both are normal. Do what you can. Leave the rest.
  </p>
  <p>
    And know this: the 22-year-old reading from a script at the insurance company is not your enemy.
    They don't know what to say. Neither do you. Say the words. It gets slightly less strange
    each time, until one day you realize you've said it enough times that it has become,
    if not easy, at least possible.
  </p>
</div>

